image.altText: Josh Addo-Carr celebrates

items.synopsis: The Blues are playing for pride as they host a dead rubber in Sydney, with Queensland shooting for just their fifth Origin clean sweep in more than 40 years. Follow live.

title.children: Blues lead Queensland in pulsating Origin Game III

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Down the left again, Cody Walker gave James Tedesco early ball and the Blues skipper, who's copped a fair bit of flak this series, turned Daly Cherry-Evans and Valentine Holmes inside out, breaking through the line and sending Bradman Best in for another one. That feels like the game-sealing try, as Stephen Crichton converts for a 24-10 NSW lead .
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: TEDESCO BREAKS THROUGH AND SETS UP BEST'S DOUBLE ON DEBUT!!

children.content: Down the left again, Cody Walker gave James Tedesco early ball and the Blues skipper, who's copped a fair bit of flak this series, turned Daly Cherry-Evans and Valentine Holmes inside out, breaking through the line and sending Bradman Best in for another one.
That feels like the game-sealing try, as
Stephen Crichton converts for a 24-10 NSW lead

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Nope. Hamiso Tabuai-Fidow batted the dropout back, and it ended up in the hands of Isaah Yeo. But Stephen Crichton knocked on in the aerial contest. And it's a penalty to Queensland because Yeo was offside.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 62' The Blues score off a short dropout ... or do they?

children.content: Hamiso Tabuai-Fidow batted the dropout back, and it ended up in the hands of Isaah Yeo. But Stephen Crichton knocked on in the aerial contest.
And it's a penalty to Queensland because Yeo was offside.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Val Holmes poked his nose through and got a (possibly forward) ball away to Murray Taulagi, who flew upfield and beat James Tedesco, but he slowed up enough for the defenders to catch him. DCE earns Queensland a repeat set with a grubber into the in-goal for Nanai, who throws Tedesco dead.
